<%provide(:title, "Digital device requirements")%>
<style type="text/css">
	.title-header{
		font-size: 3em;
		font-weight: bold;
		/*text-transform: uppercase;*/
		margin-bottom: 20px;
		padding-bottom: 20px;
		position: relative;
		text-align: center;
	}
	.header-text{
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 400;
		/*font-size: 1rem!important;*/
		letter-spacing: .03125em!important;
		line-height: 1.5rem;
	}
	.checklist li{
		font-size: 20px;
		/*letter-spacing: .03125em!important;*/
		line-height: 2rem;
		font-weight: bold;
	}

</style>
<div class="container">
	
	
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-12">
			<h1 class="title-header mt-5 mb-2">Digital Device Requirement</h1>
			<p class="text-center header-text mb-3 text-muted">
				There are certain requirements you have to fulfill in order to be addmitted to YIC-Online and start Learning. Make sure that you meet the minimum requirements before starting your application process.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="col-12 col-md-8 offset-sm-2">
			<div class="card card-primary">
				<div class="card-header">
					<h3 class="card-title">
						<i class="fas fa-info-circle mr-2"></i>
						<strong>Digital Device Requirement</strong>
					</h3>
				</div>
				<div class="card-body mt-2">
					<p style="font-size: 20px;"><strong>Dear Student,</strong></p>

					<p class="text-muted">I understand that it is my responsibility to have a computer with a webcam, stable internet connection, sufficient technical ability to navigate through the system and accomplish my duties. I take full responsibility and agree this conditions as I proceed.</p>
					<ol class="checklist">
						<li>Good knowledge on how to use digital devices and the internet.</li>
						<li>Good internet connection at least once a week.</li>
						<li>A laptop with Webcam.</li>
					</ol>
					<h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem!important;font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: .0125em!important;">Please <%= link_to "Click here >>", digital_iteracy_quiz_path%>to take Digital Literacy Test.</h3>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>